      </draw:image>
     </draw:frame> (MBFIA) is an all-volunteer non-profit education organization that provides assistance <text:s/>and funding for activities which enhance the quality of visits to <text:s/>McArthur Burney Falls Memorial State Park, Castle Crags State Park and Ahjumawi Lava Springs State Park. The association was founded in 1984 <text:s/>to promote greater appreciation of the cultural and natural history of the region.</text:p>
