    <text:p text:style-name="P213"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P161" text:outline-level="2" text:is-list-header="true"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1270_2834373222"/>Donations<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1270_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">We are a group of volunteers who love and support our northern California State Parks. We operate gift shops, sell firewood and do other fund-raisers to help us help the parks! </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">All donations are used for educational and interpretive activities in the Park. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">Did you enjoy the campfire and evening programs? These are supported by donations. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">Did you or your child complete the Discovery Quest Challenge? The patch you received was paid for with donations.</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">Did you take a nature walk or a guided canoe trip on Lake Britten? These are supported by donations. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">Is this Visitor Guide newspaper helpful and interesting? Donations paid for printing the paper. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">Did you attend Heritage Day? Donations provide candle-making, beading, saw-bucking, rope-making, pine-doll building, apple cider press, and old time fiddle music. This celebration of life in the Intermountain Area in the 1870’s is provided thanks to donations.</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">Donations for the Park are accepted by the McArthur-Burney Falls Interpretive Association. An organization of volunteers from the communities around the Park, the Association is also known as the Friends of the Falls. We love the Park and we know that you do as well.</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">We encourage every visitor to make a donation in any amount to support activities in the Park. Checks may be made payable to MBFIA, Box 777, Burney CA 96013. Donation envelopes are available in the kiosk at the entrance or in the Visitor Center. We will list donors in next year’s Visitor Guide.</text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P97" text:outline-level="2"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P98" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1187_2834373222"/>Board Members<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1187_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L2">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">President Jim Sacson</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">Vice President: Mark Downie</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">Secretary: Ann Sacson</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">Treasurer Emiritus: Jaci White</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">Webmaster: Bob Boyce</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P298"><text:span text:style-name="T93">Tablemaster: </text:span>Bill McSweeney</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P300">Media Rep: Craig Harrington</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P300">Newsletter Editor: <text:span text:style-name="T62">Tony Otto</text:span></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P301">Volunteer: Susan Lamke</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">Alice Hoveman</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P297">Jill Overbaugh</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P299">Tom Stockton</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1272_2834373222"/>Firewood <text:span text:style-name="T94">at the Falls</text:span><text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1272_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T15">The MFBIA has firewood </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T82">in</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T75">0.8 cubic foot</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T74"> </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T75">ba</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T74">g</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T75">s</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T15"> availa</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T16">ble </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T93">just past the entrance kiosk and at the upper and lower campground areas when open.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T82">The cost is </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T75">$10/</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T77">one</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T82"> bag, </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T75">$18/</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T77">two</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T82"> bags, and </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T75">$25/</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T77">three</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T82"> bags.</text:span></text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P214"><text:span text:style-name="T16">The firewood is gathered </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T94">from trees grown in the park. In the fall, the park staff identifies hazard trees, those that threaten people or structures, and fells them during the winter. The MBFIA, in partnership with the Department of Corrections, crews from the local CAL Fire camps buck and split these trees into firewood bundles for your use.</text:span></text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P173" text:outline-level="2"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P174" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1191_2834373222"/><text:soft-page-break/>Mission<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1191_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P138">The objectives.of the Association are:</text:p>
    <text:list text:style-name="L3">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P302">Promote the educational and interpretive activities of the State Park System, principally in McArthur Burney Falls Memorial State Park, Castle Crags State Park and Ahjumawi Lava Springs State Park</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P302"><text:span text:style-name="T55">T</text:span>hrough effective leadership and operation of the McArthur Burney Falls Interpretive Association. </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P303">Actively engage in fundraising activities to provide financial support for:</text:p>
      <text:list>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P303">Heritage Day</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P303">Interpretive Staff and Programs</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P303">Volunteer in Parks Program Support</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P303">Visitor Center</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P303">Other support expenses</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
      </text:list>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:p text:style-name="P139"/>
    <text:list text:continue-numbering="true" text:style-name="L3">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P302">Plan and co-manage all events and activities of the Annual Heritage Day Event with State Park personnel at no cost to the Intermountain Community and outside visitors.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P302">Produce and make available to the park visitor, by sale or free distribution, suitable interpretive and educational literature, including books, maps, pamphlets, and DVD&apos;s.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P302">Buy, sell, and distribute state-printed and other publications, which enhance visitor knowledge of the geologic history of Burney Falls, volcanic legacy of the Cascade Range and related topics (biodiversity of Northern California).</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P304"><text:span text:style-name="T55">A</text:span>cquire display materials or objects pertaining to the Cultural History and Natural History of the Intermountain area for the purpose of adding them to the interpretive collection in the Visitor Center.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P304">Assist in the development and improvement of interpretive features, including signs, markers, and audio/visual stations, when aid is requested by the State Park system.:</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1193_2834373222"/>President’s Message<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1193_2834373222"/></text:h>
