        eUltYWdlVHlwZT51cm46Y29tOmFwcGxlOnBobw==
       </office:binary-data>
      </draw:image>
     </draw:frame>As President of the McArthur Burney Falls Interpretative Association, I am pleased to welcome visitors to the McArthur-Burney Falls Memorial State Park. <text:s/>In 1964, my family bought a home and property near the park. <text:s/>I had the tremendous opportunity of growing up here. <text:s/>My family enjoyed exploring the natural beauty and all of the outdoor activities the Intermountain area has to offer.</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P110">I served in the United States Navy after high school and had the privilege of traveling to many places around the world. <text:s/>My travels helped me appreciate how unique and untouched much of our mountain area has remained. <text:s/>It is my desire to help retain the natural beauty we get to enjoy every day.</text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P201" text:outline-level="2"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P202" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1195_2834373222"/><text:soft-page-break/>2026 MBFIA Annual Plan<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1195_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">Board Business</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L4">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Raise $86,000 through donations, sales of Visitor Center Merchandise, Firewood and Visitor Guide Ads to support Interpretive Services at McArthur-Burney Falls Memorial, Castle Crags and Ahjumawi Lava Springs State Parks.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Continue to recruit and expand Board membership with focus on public relations and financial expertise.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Hire a bookkeeping service to manage revenue and expenditure throughout the season.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Focus on Board development to provide leadership for Board projects; succession planning and training for transitioning of responsibilities.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Provide opportunities for donations from the public on the MBFIA website and donatio<text:span text:style-name="T69">n </text:span>envelopes at the park with a goal of raising $3,500.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Raise $2,500 coordinating the sale of one memorial table at MBF.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Develop policies and procedures that will enable the sale of Memorial Benches for implementation in 2026.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Continue partnership with the Mountain Jewels Ranch to recycle 4,000 pounds of plastic, aluminum and glass raising $2,100.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Solicit a minimum of 9 businesses raising $3,000 for Visitor Guide Advertising at MBF.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P306">Continue to invest $20,000 in money market account @4% interest.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">Visitor Centers Reopening</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L5">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P307">Operate full-time Visitor Center Gift Shops at McArthur Burney Falls and Castle Crags State Parks with goal of raising $37,000.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P307">Provide access to MBF Visitor Center for 12,000 visitors, 5 days a week.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P307">Expand sale merchandise inventory and continue to support the new T-shirt designs at both MBF and Castle Crags.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">Firewood Production and Sales</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L6">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P308">Provide funding in the amount of $12,000 for processing 4,000 bundles of firewood for sale to campers at MBF and Castle Crags State Parks.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P308">Manage the sale of Firewood, stocking weekly supplies at campsites and entry wood sheds, with a goal of raising $37,000 in revenue.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">Interpretive Services Projects</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L7">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P309">Support the design and/or replacement of two Interpretive Panels in McArthur-Burney Falls and one panel in Castle Crags State Parks.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P309">Finish the replacement/repair the campfire benches; mill wood from downed trees providing material for replacement and repair of decaying benches in the campfire arena to complete the project.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">Interpretive Program Support</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L8">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P310">Print 35,000 20-page Visitor Guides for Mc Arthur Burney Falls Memorial State Park.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P310">Order 2,000 2026 Discovery Challenge Patches for MBF.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P310">Revise the Discovery Challenge Quiz Questions in the MBF.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P310"><text:soft-page-break/>Provide funding in the amount of $1,000 to Shasta Wildlife Rescue and Rehabilitation to hold 10 camp fire presentations with live birds and animals for campers at MBF and Castle Crags State Park.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P310">Plan and schedule Heritage Day in October for 1200 visitors. Continue to re-envision the day with a broader look at the natural and human impact on the land, keeping in place what has been a successful involvement by local folks.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P310">Support at least 2 Art In The Park events at MBF State park in cooperation with local <text:span text:style-name="T70">artists.</text:span></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">SPECIAL PROJECTS</text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">In partnership with the State Park district, define and propose special projects that could be funded or managed by the Association at each park. Possible projects could include:</text:p>
    <text:list text:style-name="L9">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P311">Develop Volunteer Work Days that include minor amenities for the bathrooms, trash pick-up on the trails, beach rehabilitation, campfire bench repair and/or other such work projects.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P311"><text:s/>Support volunteers and staff at both parks during the season that will include water/drinks/snacks and end of season BBQ.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P311">Develop plans to build memorial benches from local downed trees for interested customers in both parks.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="P157" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1197_2834373222"/>Board Meeting Highlights<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1197_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">January <text:span text:style-name="T88">2026</text:span></text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L10">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jim introduced Tony Otto and asked him to tell us a little about his background. <text:s/>Tony <text:span text:style-name="T95">visited the area on </text:span>grade school <text:span text:style-name="T95">summer vacations</text:span> and recently <text:span text:style-name="T95">moved to the area</text:span> two and a half years ago. <text:s/>He hopes to help by working with the Web<text:span text:style-name="T95">m</text:span>aster and working on brochures.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Most <text:span text:style-name="T96">budget</text:span> items <text:span text:style-name="T96">for 2026 </text:span>will <text:span text:style-name="T96">be</text:span> the same as 2025. <text:s/>However, we do not have to contribute this year to the contingency fund as it was not used in 2025.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Costs on lunches and bbq for events could be reduced by preparing less expensive items. <text:s/>Terri suggested hamburgers and hotdogs.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Heritage Day vendor costs went up last year. <text:s/>We also replaced some needed equipment for Heritage Day. <text:s/>Castle Crags did not use the budget that was allocated.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Printing costs are expected to increase. <text:s/>Craig told us to expect about a 3% increase. <text:s/>Bids are good for 30 days.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Marlon said he would check on the design for 100 year anniversary patches. <text:s/>An order for 2,000 was agreed upon. Each patch is between $1.88 and $1.94 for our costs.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">There are also sales items that need to be ordered to replace stock in the Visitor Center.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jaci mentioned that she would check with the T-shirt artist about 100 year anniversary update to our shirts.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jaci also let us know that Alice would prepare the certificate for Heritage Day, 2026.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Additional <text:span text:style-name="T96">firewood</text:span> bags are needed. <text:s/>Jaci mentioned that we usually order 6,000. </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">There is recycling that needs to be handled. <text:s/>Jaci acquired a recycling certificate. <text:s/>However, future recycling does not look viable because of the distance and lack of ability to transport at this time. <text:s/>Jim asked to table discussion for now.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P313"><text:soft-page-break/>No <text:span text:style-name="T96">Memorial Picnic Tables</text:span> were sold <text:span text:style-name="T96">in 2025</text:span>. <text:s/>There is one family interested at this time. <text:s/>The cost is somewhat of a concern. <text:s/>Our cost is $1,400 and $2,800 is what we are charging. <text:s/>We have had five tables ordered over the past <text:span text:style-name="T96">five</text:span> years. <text:s/>Bill said he would get a current price for this year. <text:s/>There is continued interest in benches. <text:s/>However, a process has to be followed to prepare groundwork <text:s/>for any changes or installation.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Volunteer Day was set for September 12, 2026. <text:s/>Bill also plans to be in the Park with his brother the full week before Memorial Day.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jim mentioned that he is getting estimates for replacing technical equipment as needed. <text:s/>The State has to do the actual set up of any equipment. <text:s/>Andy Urlie let Jim know that he would be willing to make an updated video for the Visitor Center.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P313">Blair joined the meeting. <text:s/></text:p>
      <text:list>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P313">He let us know that the weather was allowing the Parks to keep busy. <text:s/>Blair is asking for the same staffing for 2026 and is very optimistic for this year.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P312">Bob asked Blair about the Lottery system problems that people were encountering. <text:s/>In general, everything should be pushed to be answered by the Parks. <text:s/></text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P312">Golden Poppy folks will still need a reservation.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P312">Blair discussed the 100 year Celebration. <text:s/>Nothing is concrete at this time. </text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P312">Ideas for the 100 year Celebration were discussed but all items must be presented and approved by the State through Blair.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P312">Blair mentioned that one of the Sr. Park Aides mentioned that an electric bicycle would allow quieter campground checks. <text:s/></text:p>
       </text:list-item>
      </text:list>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Interpretive signage was discussed. <text:s/>If the MBFIA is willing, we can continue to fund additional signage.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Craig mentioned old stands or signage might be desirable to purchase by visitors or supporters of the Park. <text:s/>Most of the boards are in bad condition. <text:s/>Blair said that the current plan is to use them as backing or bulletin boards. <text:s/>However, he would consider sales if there was an interest.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jaci mentioned that the cost and beauty of the new signage ($12,000 per year) has been disappointing due to the finished artwork not being installed quickly and properly. <text:s/>Blair said that this could now be addressed with the State. <text:s/>It was previously a Union issue and can now be addressed as not being an item for “in house” installation.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jaci let us know that the MBFIA received a nice thank you note from Mary. <text:s/></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P314">Tony was approved as a new board member.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P312">Jaci asked if someone could set up a central location where all members could access documents. <text:s/>Bob mentioned that Tony could possibly do it. <text:s/>However, it should not be part of the website.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">February 2026</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L11">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Jim asked Blair to share the California Report. <text:span text:style-name="T103">Basically 2026 is not appropriate for a Centenial celebration.</text:span></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Bob Boyce mentioned that 1923 was the date the land was transferred to the State.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Celebrating 100 years has been difficult to pinpoint. <text:s/>Blair said the original date of <text:soft-page-break/>1920, would have created difficulty in 2020 because of COVID restrictions.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Although the property became part of the State in 1926, nothing happened in 1926. <text:s/>In 1927 there was a Bill put forward and passed that turned Burney Falls land into a State Park.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Jaci then asked if the entire Park system would celebrate in 2027. <text:s/>Blair explained that the Department uses the 1864 date due to the Yosemite Grant from a messaging standpoint. <text:s/>However, the 1927 has been acknowledged by the department as the modern State Parks date.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Bob suggested and asked if we could recognize the 250th anniversary of the United States during Heritage Day. <text:s/>Blair said we could include that theme for Heritage Day.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair let us know Memorial Day will continue to be challenging until <text:span text:style-name="T96">a reservation </text:span>system is set up. <text:s text:c="2"/>Jaci asked if there would be any staffing changes. <text:s/>Blair said staffing should remain the same. <text:s/>Additional staffing support is expected if needed.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Bob asked when reservations for camping for both parks would start. <text:s/>Blair let us know <text:s/>it begins with May 15, 2026.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Mark suggested a sample could be done with guests returning tags. <text:s/>Blair said there had been some operational issues with the tags being returned in the past.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair is hoping to begin postings for the season and begin hires in late March or early April. <text:s/>The Senior Park Aides will start back in March. <text:s/>Marlon will be back full time in March as well. <text:s/>Everyone hopes to have the Visitors Guide completed before Memorial Day. </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Jaci let us know Alice will do an article to thank those who contributed donations.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair encouraged us to reach out to Marlon as needed.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Signage was discussed. <text:s/>Storms have kept installations postponed. <text:s/>The Worker 1 at Castle Crags has been contacted and once the Castle Crags signage is installed, he will help install the completed Burney Falls signage.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair also let us know that Ranger James also has committed to helping Blair accomplish this goal.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair mentioned that he would make sure that Gregory Wolf of the Tribal Council had contact information with the MBFIA. <text:s/>He gave permission for Jim to meet with him at the Park.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Jim let us know he has also been looking at contact information with the California League of Park Associations. <text:s/>The networking component is helpful to possibly see how other associations handle similar problems or situations. <text:s/>There are some resources for Nonprofit &amp;/or fundraising ideas.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair mentioned he was trying to set up a meeting from the California State Park Foundation. <text:s/>It is a big organization and may have helpful resources for our association.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Finances were discussed. <text:s/>The 2026 Budget is based on the 2025 budget. <text:s/>There is money dedicated for signage. <text:s/>Some adjustments have been made for signage. <text:s/>Costs were less for previously designed work.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315"><text:soft-page-break/>An $5,000 allowance for a bookkeeper at $20/hour was added. <text:s/>A General Manager instead of a bookkeeper could be considered at $20K to $30K per year.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Our Budget is solvent but we would need someone who is proficient with Quickbooks to handle our Finances.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Blair suggested touching base with other Boards to see how this is handled with other associations.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Board Recruitment was discussed. <text:s/>Advertising in the local paper &amp; posting on bulletin boards was suggested. <text:s/>The quarterly Newsletter also could be a place to recruit.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Tony mentioned to continue to send ideas &amp; photos for the Newsletters. <text:s/>He will save all the items for the 100 year celebration for 2027. </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Firewood was discussed. <text:s/>The Budget reflects having about 4,000 bundles. <text:s/>Crags is not known but Blair said he could touch base to find out. <text:s/>They have trees down that can be used for bundles at Crags.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Recycling was discussed. <text:s/>Terri received the go ahead to take items to Redding for recycling. </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Volunteer Day was discussed. <text:s/>Bill will set the time. <text:s/>Hot dogs &amp; Hamburgers were suggested for this year’s appreciation lunch.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Insurance was discussed. <text:s/>Mark let us know it stays the same for this year.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">T-shirts were okayed by Parks for this year. <text:s/>Other ideas for using the same artwork were discussed and the design was approved by Blair.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Jim asked Blair about the date for opening of the Visitor Center. <text:s/>He replied that as soon as possible. <text:s/>Possibly April if we can get volunteers to regular days.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">Craig had some ideas using square. <text:s/>Jaci said our credit card system is good through 2028.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P315">The CD is up for potential changes April 20, 2026. <text:s/>There is a two week window for changes.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3">March 2026</text:h>
    <text:list text:style-name="L12">
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">The current slate of officers was approved for 2026.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">Business cards have been done for Jim, Ann, and Tony. They will be available to other directors at the April meeting.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">The board approved a job description for a paid seasonal non-profit treasurer if one can not be found to replace Jaci on the board. The Quickbooks website may provide a list of bookkeeping services.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">Volunteer flyer posters will be placed at key businesses and bulletin boards in the region.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">The current budget was review, discussed, and approved.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">Tom was added as an additional director to co-sign checks.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P318">Rolling over the current CD at USBank was discussed and approved.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P319">Recycling had been discussed in previous meetings. The feeling had been that the gain wasn’t worth the effort. The situation has changed:</text:p>
      <text:list>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P319">The current Chief of Maintenance definitely wants us to continue.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P319">North State is giving us a better rate.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P319">Mt Jewel was excited to receive their portion.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P319"><text:soft-page-break/>The board consensus was to continue pursuing our involvement in recycling.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
      </text:list>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P319">The Visitor Center opening is targeted for Friday, April 3, 2026. Several volunteers are willing but scheduling availability needs to be done.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P320">Memorial tables were discussed. Hopefully this newsletter will bring more interest. Tables are ordered on the website and Bob, webmaster, forwards the information to Bill, the tablemaster, to fulfill the order. <text:span text:style-name="T20">Ed. Note: See the Memorial Tables section above for details.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T87"> </text:span></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P321">Blair joined the meeting to brief the Board on State Parks issues.</text:p>
      <text:list>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P321">He gave the California Report.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P321">The position for an additional Senior Aide for the Visitor Center is <text:span text:style-name="T103">still pending. C</text:span>urrent aides and new hires should be in place for the beginning of May.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P321">The previous Camp Hosts, Matt &amp; Cheryl, <text:s/>have taken a position handling Cabin Rentals. So, additional Camp Hosts need to be hired. Blair is activly recruting for available summer spots. </text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P316">Crags is looking good. <text:s/>Almost everyone is returning. <text:s/>Their permanent Maintenance guy is ready to help with installation of signage, <text:span text:style-name="T86">both at Crags and the Falls.</text:span></text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P322">Blair suggested that our board consult with the Redwood Humboldt Association and consider their arrangement with their parks.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
       <text:list-item>
        <text:p text:style-name="P322">Blair reminded the board that the California State Parks Foundation is available for help. <text:s/>We have multiple options and tremendous potential for the future.</text:p>
       </text:list-item>
      </text:list>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Some of the obstacles for having an employee <text:span text:style-name="T88">(paid Accountant)</text:span> working for the association were discussed. <text:s/>Mark agreed to looking into compliance and Jim said we would table the discussion for now.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Firewood sales may be banned if <text:span text:style-name="T88">the State declares a </text:span>dry, hot season. <text:s/>The park staff will lock the sheds if required to do so. <text:s/>This may require the association to diversify revenue.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Blair let <text:span text:style-name="T88">the board</text:span> know that a Contractor that did the logging project at Crags wanted to donate funds for a simple rustic memorial bench. <text:s/>Jim asked Blair for additional approval for a site along the Pioneer Trail at Burney Falls to be considered as well.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P322">Blair approved the business cards. The state needs to provide business cards for Marlon.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Bob asked about QR codes that could be added to our website and added to other articles and posters. <text:s/>Tony said he would look into it. <text:span text:style-name="T28">Ed. Note: QR codes are included with the web links at the end of this newsletter.</text:span></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Tony asked board members to submit items to add to our newsletter. </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Insurance was discussed and current.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P316">Heritage Day was discussed. <text:s/>Lunch for volunteer students and staff (about 40) would be needed this year. <text:s/>An idea to give out an award to Volunteer of the Year on Heritage Day was suggested.</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P317">Jaci let us know the T-shirts were in. <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T88">Pictures will be included in this newsletter.</text:span></text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:h text:style-name="P131" text:outline-level="1"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1199_2834373222"/><text:soft-page-break/><text:span text:style-name="T63">A </text:span>Wonder of the World<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1199_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P237"><text:span text:style-name="T23">SecretSanFrancisco.com</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T19"> recently posted an article about Burney Falls. </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T39">Whether future President Teddy Roosevelt described it as the ‘Eighth’ or just <text:s/>‘A’ Wonder of the world is up to interpretation, the falls are certainly wonderous</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T19">. </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T25">Ed Note: </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">See the </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T30">On the Internet </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">section at the end for a link.</text:span></text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P162" text:outline-level="1"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1201_2834373222"/>About the Three State Parks<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1201_2834373222"/></text:h>
