       </office:binary-data>
      </draw:image>
     </draw:frame>I visited the falls and nearby Lassen park during summer vacation a couple of times as a primary grade schooler and as a junior high student. Those were great memories, along with coming around a curve on CA-299 and coming upon a VW Beetle sized boulder that had fallen on the upward lane of the highway. <text:span text:style-name="T40">I’m not sure my Dad was as amused as I was.</text:span> Fifty plus years later, the opportuntity to live in Fall River Mills came about. Now I live a few short miles from the falls. I was asked to join the Board of Directors of the MBFIA and I greatfully accepted. When the need to resume the quarterly newsletter arose, I willingly <text:span text:style-name="T40">took on</text:span> the challenge.</text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P66" text:outline-level="1"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1221_2834373222"/>Falls Visitor Center<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1221_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T59">The MBFIA operates the visitors center at the main parking lot above the falls. There you will find informative panels about the , the park, and the local flora &amp; fauna. Several art exhibits are displayed in the center, including: </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T20">Ed. Note: </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">See this quarter’s featured artist below.</text:span></text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P20" text:outline-level="2"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P21" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1223_2834373222"/><text:soft-page-break/>Visitor Center Store<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1223_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P240"><text:span text:style-name="T48">T</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T42">he 2026 T-Shirts are now available at the Visitor Center Store.</text:span></text:p>
