    <text:h text:style-name="P215" text:outline-level="1"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P217" text:outline-level="1"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1227_2834373222"/>Featured Artist this Quarter: <text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1227_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P27">Marla Nolan</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P179">I am a disabled artist living in Northern California with my wonderful husband Tim and black shelter cat Meowtian. <text:s/>I retired from my beloved career as Pharmacist in 2015 due to worsening chronic illness. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P179">I have been creative my whole life. When I was still working, before my hands lost fine function and developed deformities from arthritis, I was often working on needle work, usually of a famous painting. Here is the last piece I completed:</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P179">After I left work, an artist friend gave me a Sumi-E book thinking this might be something I could do. Enjoying it but wanting color, I found an online watercolor work at your own pace course in 2019. I fell in love with the beautiful transparency and glow of the medium. <text:s/>I became excited that you could <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr8" draw:name="Image17" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="0.0075in" svg:y="0.0319in" svg:width="1.75in" svg:height="1.5098in" draw:z-index="35"><draw:image draw:mime-type="image/jpeg">
