     </draw:frame><text:span text:style-name="T90">Visitor </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T91">Services </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T90">Senior </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T91">Park </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T90">Aide</text:span><text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc6136_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P326">The Visitor Services Senior Park Aide (Seasonal) is expected to work weekends, holidays, and evenings if necessary and assigned days off may vary from month to month. The Visitor Services Senior Park Aide (Seasonal) will perform duties dressed in full State Park uniform.</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P326">Primary duties include but are not limited to: Park Aide Lead and administrative duties such as maintaining accountability worksheets, attendance records, and Park Aide schedule, training new Park Aide staff, providing direction and assistance to Park Aide staff, and receptionist duties for the office. The Senior Park Aide (Seasonal) will also</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P326">operate the entrance station, greet visitors, and provide information about park conditions, closures, trails, and rules and regulations. In addition, the Senior Park Aide (Seasonal) should be proficient in basic use of a computer and able to check work e-mail account.</text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_1" text:outline-level="1"/>
    <text:h text:style-name="P218" text:outline-level="1"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1239_2834373222"/><text:soft-page-break/>Memorial <text:span text:style-name="T16">Tables</text:span><text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1239_2834373222"/></text:h>
