    <text:h text:style-name="P197" text:outline-level="1" text:is-list-header="true"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1241_2834373222"/>Tribute<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1241_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1243_2834373222"/>A Tribute to Generations of Families Who Vacation At Burney Falls<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1243_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P207">For over forty years and probably more, families have gathered at McArthur Burney Falls Memorial State Park to spend time together. Grandparents, Uncles &amp; Aunts, Cousins, Moms, Pops, and children camping, swimming, fishing, hiking, cooking, sleeping under the stars, roasting marshmallows, singing, and making strong memories. You may find their names on tables and benches throughout the park in memory of loved ones.</text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P230">We would like to acknowledge the families that call this park home and have supported its interpretive services for at least the last ten years. The ones we know about are listed below. If you are not on the list, please let us know who you are and how long your family has been trekking to Northern California to spend time at our beautiful park. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P230">Just complete the <text:s/>form below or email the information to friends@ burneyfallspark.org</text:p>
