     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P325">The Taube Family</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P325">The Towle Family – In Memory of Tom Garcia – 116 years </text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P325">The Van Aken Family – 62 years</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P325">The Vitale Family – In Memory of Scott Lunger – 29 years</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P325">The Wilbur Family – In Memory of Linda Wilbur - 51 years</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
     <text:list-item>
      <text:p text:style-name="P325">The Zwanziger Family – In honor of grandchildren Callen, Kassidy, Kamille and Chase- 60 years</text:p>
     </text:list-item>
    </text:list>
    <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Thank you all for your love and support of this beautiful park.</text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1247_2834373222"/>Friends of the Falls<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1247_2834373222"/></text:h>
    <text:p text:style-name="P145">Friends <text:s/>of Burney Falls provides education <text:s/>and interpretation and our programs highlight the Park&apos;s natural and cultural <text:s/>elements. Burney Falls offers hiking trails, flora and fauna, birds, squirrels and the like, camping, <text:s/>cabins and Lake Britton. <text:s/>Funds donated support Interpretive and educational activities, <text:s/>including guided hikes, Junior Ranger programs, campfire and craft <text:s/>activities, sing-alongs and group games. At Burney Falls, our Visitor Center includes a Gift Shop, as well as information about the geology, flora and fauna, <text:s/>cultural history and recreational opportunities in the park and the <text:s/>surrounding area. Our annual Heritage Day celebration in October offers <text:s/>weaving, cross-cut sawing, branding, candle-making, pine-doll making, apple cider pressing and Dutch Oven cooking. <text:s/>The Park has instituted a birding program, that includes <text:soft-page-break/>guided bird <text:s/>identification walks, loaner binoculars plus a library of information. <text:s/>In addition, we have supported new native plants around the Visitor <text:s/>Center, with information about the plantings available for visitors. </text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P145">We&apos;re also in the process of renewing our availability for sale and placement of memorial benches and picnic tables at the Park. Contact us for more details. <text:s/></text:p>
    <text:h text:style-name="P30" text:outline-level="1"><text:bookmark-start text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1274_2834373222"/>Contact Infomation<text:bookmark-end text:name="__RefHeading___Toc1274_2834373222"/></text:h>
